+ Savannah Cave Microdungeons!: There are now structures in Savannah Caves, at least, the start of them. I hope you enjoy bones!
# Structures
+ 20 Normal Structures
+ 2 Rare Structures

+ New Enhancement Packs!: Some existing back items, and new craftable back items have been added to the Enhancement Pack list!
# Vanilla Back Items
+ Stargazer Acolyte Wings: +10% Jump Height, +10% Max Energy
+ Stargazer Priest Wings: +20% Jump Height, +15% Max Energy
+ Stargazer Prophet Wings: +25% Jump Height, +20% Max Energy, -10% Fall Damage
+ Shawl of Elation: +15% Damage Boost, +15% Run Boost, Glow 
+ Fire Lord's Cloak: +20% Damage Boost, Fire Immunity, Lava Immunity
# New Back Items
+ Aurium Defender: +10% All Elemental Resistance
+ Aquari Battlestandard: Swim Boost, Maelstrom
+ Vermillium Shell: +10% Max HP, Noxious
+ Violium Climbing Gear: +20% Jump Boost, +10% Run Boost, -50% Fall Damage
+ Portable Uranium Generator: +25% Max Energy, Energy Recharge

+ Reworked Hazard Warning System!: Tired of all of those hazard messages from SAIL? Well, no more! When under a hazard's effects, a small visual and audio cue will play. Now the radio message is only relegated to be played once!

+ New Music!: Thanks to Gigaroni, a composer for my other big mod, Ancient Cosmos. This mod now has its own music! More to come.
# New Track
+ Mesoscale Convection: Plays on Anabatic planets

+ New Blocks!: There are now a few new blocks, mainly centered around the new savannah structures.
# Blocks
+ Large Vertebra
+ Large Bone Material
+ Peat

+ New Status Effects!
# Effects
+ Maelstrom: Deal massive damage while Wet, and half the bonus when Damp.
+ Noxious: A thorns effect that poisons enemies.

+ Light Tool Visual Updates!: New sprites have been made for pretty much every light tool in the game.
# Visuals Updated
+ Lantern: Now looks closer to a hurricane lamp, though kept many of its original design choices.
+ Flashlight: Given a Protectorate coat of paint.
+ Flashlight (Green): Similar to its vanilla counterpart. Made for visibility.
+ Flashlight (Red): A dark design, for the stealthy purposes red light serves.
+ Flashlight (Yellow): Made into an old aluminium flashlight. 
+ Flare: Given a new look that makes more sense as a modern flare. 

+ Spirit Element Implementation!: In Hylotl Castles, where one can usually find katanas. You can find a rare variant that is guaranteed to have the spirit element. With its own spirit variants of the normal abilities! As well, Hylotl Warlords now come equipped with these katanas.


